Mangalore Refinery & Petrochemicals
Ltd. (MRPL)  is seeking to buy 600,000 barrels each of low-sulfur and
high-sulfur crude for loading July 1 and July 15, according to
documents e-mailed to potential sellers. The two cargoes are to
be discharged at New Mangalore port on  India â€™s west coast. The
tender closes at 9:30 a.m. local time on May 20 and offers are
valid until 8 p.m. on May 22.  To contact the reporter on this story:
